	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Johannesburg - Five motorists were charged with
reckless and negligent driving, with one clocked at 154km/h in an 80km/h zone
in Parkland, Johannesburg, Metro police said on Sunday. "Metro police officers... monitored the Zuurfontein
Road when they stopped a BMW sedan driven by a 34-year old male for clocking
154km/h," Lieutenant Kobeli Mokhesang said. Mokhesang said the driver claimed he was rushing to
hospital to see a friend. He said the incident happened at 09:20 on Sunday. "Other drivers were caught doing speeds of between
113km/h and 126km/h," he said.The speedsters were taken to the Sebenza police station and will appear in the
Edenvale Magistrate's Court soon. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  